org.modelio.api.module.context.project

Interface IFragmentStructure


  • public interface IFragmentStructure
    This interface describes a Fragment in a project: ie a name, a version, a type...
    Since:
    3.5

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      java.lang.String getName()
      Get the fragment name.
      java.lang.String getRemoteLocation()
      Get the fragment's URI in the opened project.

    • Method Detail

      • getName

        java.lang.String getName()
        Get the fragment name.
        Returns:
        a name.

      • getType

        java.lang.String getType()
        Get the fragment type identifier.

        Might be EXML, EXML_URL, EXML_SVN, RAMC or MDA.

        Returns:
        the fragment type.

      • getRemoteLocation

        java.lang.String getRemoteLocation()
        Get the fragment's URI in the opened project.
        Returns:
        the mounted URI or null if the fragment is not mounted.

      • getState

        java.lang.String getState()
        Get the state of the fragment.

        Should be UP_FULL, UP_LIGHT or DOWN.

        Returns:
        the fragment state.

      • getRoots

        java.util.List<Element> getRoots()
        Get the root elements of the fragment.
        Returns:
        the root elements of the fragment.
